body:
Two actions fired in case if have mouse binding with and without modifier. This seems to be different from key bindings behavior.
üñ∞üñ∞
In particular attempt to bind <kbd>Alt</kbd>+<kbd>üñ±Ô∏è Middle</kbd> to `Paste` action alongside with default <kbd>üñ±Ô∏è Middle</kbd> binding, triggers both actions (first is `PasteSelection` and second `Paste`). Intention was to simulate `xterm`/`rxvt` behavior I used to instead of pressing <kbd>^ Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>‚áß Shift</kbd>+<kbd>V</kbd> as per default configuration.

Related issue: #1462 

### System

OS: Linux
Version: 0.3.2
Linux: X11, notion WM

#### Related configuration

```yaml
# ...
# All available `mods` and `action` values are documented in the key binding
# section.
mouse_bindings:
  - { mouse: Middle, action: PasteSelection }
  - { mouse: Middle, mods: Alt, action: Paste }
# ...
```

Note that I have bindings for key <kbd>F1</kbd> that looks like this:

```yaml
# ...
  - { key: F1,                      chars: "\x1bOP"                      }
# ...
  - { key: F1,       mods: Shift,   chars: "\x1b[1;2P"                   }
# ...
```
But I confirmed that I see only `^[[1;2P` without `^[OP` when I press <kbd>‚áß Shift</kbd>+<kbd>F1</kbd>.

